caption: Exceptional food and exceptional service!! Everything from A-Z was perfect. We brought two vegans in our party and they ate just as good as we did. The staff was constantly passing by making sure glasses were filled, bread on the table and food came out to expectation. Highly highly recommended place to eat!!!
Amazing service.  Fancy !!!
Love this place! My Go TO every time I visit New Orleans. Great food, ambiance, and service.
Absolutely fabulous! I've never had a better dining experience - amazing food, drinks, atmosphere and the service was hands down the best. I can't wait to go back!

Pretty disappointing experience. Had a birthday dinner here with a party of 8. The service was poor at best, the entrees we ordered came out after an extensive wait, they did not know who ordered what. The wine we had ordered they served out of decanters and the refills of both water and wine were hars to come by. There was no check on how the food was, by the time desert was offered and ordered it had been a near eternity. The coffee and desert we ordered were also slowly served and the 2 coffees came out after the deserts (by about 5-10 minutes) As part of the reservation for the birthday a request for a bottle champagne was ignored and no recognition of the reservation requests was made. The food I would call adequate but the service was just bad. Overall fairly disappointing

Amazing rerto-vibe , good service from relaxed and kind waiters. Death by Gumbo is an amazing dish along with their salads and pecan desserts. However they won't fill you up but will leave your palates happy.

Tried the turtle soup, it tasted like lentils and wine, did not taste the turtle nor did it have turtle meat in it, it was a total disappointment. I didn't even finish it.  Had the seared foisgrass tasted great, loved it. again the portion was two small the added bread under it to make it appear as more was undesirable. Your already serving bread at the table why would you put more bread on it.  Had the bone marrow it was tasty but cooked for to long. one half of a bone is not enough. There is literally  just about a table spoon of edible food on this. did not come as pictured on their site.  We both had the short ribs and lobster. The rib was excellent and the portion adequate.  The lobster was undercooked and the portion was not sufficient.  two small bites was not enough. don't mind the raw part, I eat real sushi. but others might have issues with this.  Had an espresso coffee after dinner. It was good but rediculess amount. Who serves less than a half of a tiny cup of espresso? This was less than one tiny sip This cup should  have come full. Disappointed again. Barely a taste of coffee.  The service was excellent, the staff amazing. I overlooked the flaws of the meal because of them. Because of these many flaws I should have removed 2 stars, but because of the staff I'm only removing 1  For the cost, the food and portions should be spot on. I go to these places to eat odd foods, I expect to taste those thing in the dishes I also expect enough to be able to enjoy it.
It was out of ordinary. Really good service. Food was exceptional, everything that we tasted were really good.

The restaurant down the the service was awesome. I has the wagyu short rib with lobster tails leeks and bitter greens. I paired it with a red wine. I was amazing. The short ribs literally melted in your mouth. There was also a squash sauce spread across the plate that was awesome.
One of the best meals we've ever had. Did the 40oz tomahawk Ribeye for 2.  Service was excellent.  Reservations highly recommended.

I've been to just about every "must try" restaurant in New Orleans and I think Restaurant R'evolution is the best, hands down.  We just ate here for the 5th or 6th time and continue to be impressed.  The cocktails, food and service were next level, and have been everytime we've visited.

Totally amazing from the moment we walked in. The decor and ambience are perfection. Totally upscale and luxurious. Our servers, Tina and Jae, were the best. Funny, kind, fast and knowledgeable. We started with the charbroiled oysters, I had the red fish and my husband had the scallops. Everything was delicious, plated gorgeously and perfect. One of the best restaurants we’ve ever have been too. A must if you are in NOLA!!

Oh my goodness this restaurant was absolutely perfect! Not only was the food amazing but the staff went above and beyond! We own a restaurant and I’m very picky, I can not come up with one thing they need to improve on and I’m a tough critic. This restaurant gets a 10 out of 10 in every category. Please reward your staff and chef. They were top notch so thank you!
Amazing!!!

My wife and I had a very memorable anniversary dinner at Rest. R'evolution last night.  As most people are aware, New Orleans has it's fair share of high-end restaurants to pick and choose from in the City; I've been to my fair share of most of them.  Our dinner at R'evolution was by far one of the most high quality experiences I've had in the city.  Not only was the food fabulous but the wait staff was incredible.  If your in town and looking for a tremendous experience with food that makes it even better, don't miss this one.  I would even recommend calling ahead and ask for our waiter, Kevin and his team... He and his team gave us just the right amount of time between conversions and also were quick with recommendations both on and off menu. Kevin even selected a great wine for myself while was more than appreciate.  Worth more than 5 stars and should be one your top 5 must visits for all you foodies out there... Get the Crab Beignets, Beef TarTar and  any entree... Can't go wrong!!

We went to famously nice places, Brennan's and Commander's Palace, and of course they were amazing, but this restaurant beat both of them, in taste of food, service and atmosphere. If you can only go to one, go here for sure. Tina was our waitress and she was awesome.

I went here for a birthday dinner (pre-covid). It was a great experience! Elegant, yet cozy  atmosphere. Everything was good and our server was awesome. Loved the crab beignets and pork belly. We also enjoyed the little dessert treats they give after dinner.
This was by far the best food I have eaten in New Orleans
Lovrly ambiance fantastic food and drinks, definitely on the pricey side but worth it
Excellent food, unbelievably expensive
Was so delicious, the attention was really perfect and the food OMG! Very delicious and tasty

Classic restaurant. It’s a bit pricey and portions are on a smaller size. Amazing service. Food was ok, nothing that blew our mind. - [ 👍] Ambiance - [ 👍] Toilet - [ 👍] Service - [ ok] Food experience - [ small] Dish portions - [ 👍] Drinks - [ no] Patio availability - [ high] Expectations
The ambiance was really nice and the food was just ok for me. I ordered a glass of wine but it never came. Thankfully they didn't charge me.
Great place, loved everything about it!!!!!!
Best meal in New Orleans! There is so many fabulous flavors in this city, but the dinning experience coupled with a perfect menu is a must when visiting New Orleans.

This was the best dining experience we have had in decades! Tina, our server was fun and professional! Sam, the chef is a culinary artist! Thank you guys so much for a wonderful time and memory!!!! I’d give them 10 stars if I could. Well worth the money!!!!! The steak melts in your mouth. The quail was incredibly Devine! The appetizers were out of this world! The service was world class! Great Job!

The atmosphere from beginning to end was amazing. Issac who was one of our servers made us feel welcome and helped explain a lot of the dishes. The food was spectacular. I could not recommend a better place!

Me and my wife recently celebrated our 10 year anniversary here and was not the least disappointed. We got to take pictures with the head chef (who mind you is only 23 years old) and our server for the evening who made the experience just that much more awesome.  Amazing service amazing food amazing experience. Also recieved a signed copy of John Folse Encylepedia of cajun and creole cuisine. What more could you ask for
Basically the best restaurant in New Orleans. A must.

If you don’t mind getting covid or thinks it’s cool, this is the place for you! 1/3 of customers did not wear masks when coming in. We asked the hosts are the tables 6 feet apart at least, she shrugged and said - “sort of”.
Tiny portion sizes. Paid over a hundred dollars and walked out hungry. Dish wasn't even delicious
One of the best in town, if not the.  Everytime food drinks and service is amazing.  Frankly I'm not sure why they don't have a Michelin star yet.

My husband and I had a reservation at R'evolution for Christmas Eve dinner and were unimpressed with our experience. We are former residents of the New Orleans area, and were trying to do our part to support area restaurants upon our Christmas time visit. This was our first time dining at R'evolution, and it failed to live up to our expectations. The atmosphere is great, very beautiful. The two servers who assisted us upon arrival were great, but then the "main" wait person stepped in to take over and was lackluster at best. He complained about working on Christmas Eve, didn't have his jacket buttoned correctly, looked a bit unkept for this caliber of an establishment, couldn't answer questions about the dishes offered, and made some peculiar comments. Also disturbing was the fact that one of the servers at another table kept pulling her mask off, and of the two cooks we could see from our table, one simply wasn't wearing a mask, and the other kept running his hands through his hair - we were not too happy about either. The food itself was actually pretty bland in our opinion, and although we have eaten in many fine dining estabishments all over the world, we also thought it was over priced for the quaility, flavor, and presentation, and we certainly don't mind paying for good food. We were surprised that this was the experience we had, especially in light of the Covid situation.

What a amazing dinner we had here! Our server Alejandra and her team took care of every detail for our group of 10. Unbelievable service and the the food was even better. It doesn't get better than this. Thank you!

We had our office Christmas dinner at Revolution and it was the perfect location. The food is always top notch quality and cooked to perfection. Don’t miss the Oysters Revolution and the Crab Beignets. The steaks are cooked to perfection and everyone loved the redfish. Travis and Kevin do a great job of making the dining experience memorable. Put this on you must eat at list when in New Orleans.

We also had the duck and while it was tasty, my fiance and I fought over the last remaining morsels of the flounder.  For dessert we tossed out thoughts of calories and had the chocolate souffle which was sublime, like the rest of the dinner. While we also loved other high end restaurants in Nola but this one is our favorite.
Food was awesome service was awesome pricing reflects both. I would eat there again if given the opportunity. If you are in town and can afford it do it.
Inventive cuisine based on regional culinary classics. Good service. Pricey, of course, but a worthy occasional splurge.
Such an amazing experience and our servers were spectacular!!!

The ambiance was astonishing. It's cozy, white, airy, and bright. The bakery section was beautiful. They have art, and it looked so appealing. For me, it was the perfect pastries that I've ever seen. They were all executed with perfection. Even the packaging of the desserts was amazing! It made me wanted to buy everything. I loved it so much!

This is a culinary experience is a must while in NOLA- creole and southern creations crafted my masters in an upscale yet charming atmosphere. Service was attentive but not overbearing. Pricey, but one of the few places you definitely get your money's worth.
The Death by Gumbo was truly awesome. We also received superb service the entire time.
Had did dinner here last night. The beef tartare, scallops, and lamb were great! Service was on par with my expectations. Everyone was attentive and worked in unison. Will definitely visit again.
You gotta try wagyou

I'll  start with my staff compliments  Daniel and Charlotte  work great together!  They squeezed us in no reservations.  The drinks was amazing. Everything was prepared great! I have never had gnocchi. Probably wont again. Lol it was made beautifully,  just not my thing. They even brought us complimentary desert for our anniversary it was great! Beautiful restaurant and again GREAT STAFF and 5 star food

A group of my friends and I ate dinner here this past week. Everything about it was 5 star. Beautiful surroundings and a private room welcomed us. Our waiter, Brian Serpas, made us feel so well cared for with his great service, menu descriptions and recommendations, and just the right amount of attention. The menu is very varied and each course was delicious. If I had only one day in town, this is where I would eat.
Absolutely amazing. Cannot wait to go back.
Excellent service. Very professional. The chefs food was fresh and flavourful. Great plating great suggestions.

Buyer beware!! This is NOT the Revolution you knew before covid-19. Upon re-opening on 10/22, they will not have a GM, AGM, floor manager, or wine director. Only manager returning is the CDC. I was the wine director before covid-19. None of us were asked to come back. Good luck on your experience should you decide to go.
Outstanding place for delicious cajun food. Great place to meet and catch up with friends. Certainly worth going back to.

Came here while on a work trip. Local foodie I was working with said I had to try the death by gumbo. It's a solid 10. Presentation was awesome with a silver covered dome platter. Superb food, bit slow but friendly service, nice atmosphere. Highly recommend!
The best restaurant I've ever eat at! Hands down best service and food. The five cheese tray was amazing. Everything was great.

And we’ve been to revolution in the past and had great meals but last night was beyond awful, and I really mean beyond awful. It was extremely overpriced for the food that we ordered. The best part of our mail or the rolls and the wine. Just know that we had the charcuterie and which was awful. It only had maybe five different cheeses that were awful. I just don’t know what’s happened to this restaurant because it used to be great, and I mean great. Our two bills came to close to $700, and I was so embarrassed.
Went for Sunday brunch. Enjoyed the crab beignets and the sweet potato cappuccino accompanied by a mellow jazz trio.

Unique menu, attentive service, extensive wine list and great food. Modest portions but after a day of eating and drinking our way thru New Orleans that was ok. Despite huge wine cellar, they didnt have the wine we chose but they graciously substituted a better bottle for the same price as the one we had originally chosen. We were very happy with the entire experience.
Great food good service.
Best steak I've ever had! And I've had allot of fancy steaks!
Great restaurant. Will be back.
The food really good but super small plates

Does this place have a Michelin star? Because the experience I had felt like it. Everyone was super attentive and gave us some great recommendation. The sommelier even helped my friend choose a wine when the one my friend wanted was sold out. All the food looked like small plate but their flavor was bold and I actually got full ordering a 3 course meal. Hands down get their snapping turtle soup and chicken fried foie gras. Highly recommend.
Absolutely one of the best experiences my husband and I have ever had, food and service is exceptional would, fly down from New York just to dinner with Johnny and his team
Best restaurant in the quarter! **VIP service** the celler was exceptional.THANKS FOR THE EXPERIENCE
Delicious and a lovely experience! The lobster gnocchi was perfect. We also had a few lovely desserts.

The waiter made some recommendations that were a miss. The fried fois hides the flavor and texture of the fois. The ribeye was tough. The redfish has scales on, so don't try to eat the skin. Sauce on the fingerling potatoes was too citrusy. The au gratin potatoes have sweet potatoes in them, but it's not mentioned on the menu. The tartar was excellent.

Everything we ate was incredible. Nothing disappointed. I think we ordered everything and it was all great. Wine prices are closer to old classic steakhouse prices but it is some of the best food I have ever eaten.
Outstanding menu great service. Wonderful

An excellent meal and overall dinning experience in the French Quarter. Trust your servers recommendations as mine was perfect! Don't stress over desserts as the small sweet taste you get with the bill was plenty for my table.
Great spot for some Cajun Classics they make all their own! The Duck was Delicious!
The prices were high, food was very good.

Entire experience was first class and absolutely amazing. Special thanks to our waiters Travis and Collin as well as Chef Clayton! I enjoyed everything from the tour, to dining at the chefs table, and every single dish. Will most definitely be back in the near future!

Had stayed away after a mediocre experience fir thanksgiving. However such a holiday is not a fair test so we went back and boy we glad we did. Chef folse was in the house and every single course was a memorable experience
Delicious food and amazing service. Can't say enough about the peanut butter ice cream.
Food was fantastic, but the service was second to none. You get what you pay for, which is a total foody experience with exceptional and very knowledgeable service.
Great food, the rib eye was tasty
Food and service was top notch!!
Very well made fish. Recommend the redfish and thr swordfish.
The waiter got overwhelmed by our group of 10, and at one point was very mad, but waiting 20 mins for a simple vodka is a bit much.
Kind staff, excellent food.
Wonderful brunch and cocktails.  The gumbo was incredible.
We came for happy hour in the bar area, and it was delicious!

Oh my goodness! Definitely will be back here on our next trip here! In town for Clemson and the football championship game so the place was packed but the service was amazing. Started off with the oysters and they were the best we have ever had! We split the beet salad Nd it was soooo good! I had the swordfish with fried oysters and the combination of flavors were fabulous. Drinks were great. All in all, this place is awesome!  (Forgot to take a pic of the menu. )
Excellent service. Food overall was very good.
We visited to celebrate two birthdays and an upcoming wedding, and our waiters took great care of us. Top service!! food was delicious, can't go wrong with crab beignets and oysters.

Come to NOLA a couple times a year. First time eating at Restaurant R’evolution and it was incredible! Their turtle soup is one to rival Brennan’s and that’s saying something! Our waiter was great and super friendly. I asked him which entree was better, the lobster or the scallops and he got me a half portion of both! Who does that?
Excellent service and brunch is fabulous!

Service was great. The venison appetizer was amazing.
Amazing food & service.  Highly recommend.
Crab beignets and charbroiled oysters were delicious! The best though was the service. So warm and kind. We had an unexpectedly big group that they happily accommodated.

Good food BUT terrible service. An extremely disappointing experience! We were a big table of 8. I guess they figured they didn't need to work since the 20% tip was already built-in. We were on time but not seated until forty minutes after our reservation. Our table had no tablecloth while all others did. They removed appetizer and bread plates while there was still food on it without even asking if we were done. When the bottle of wine that we ordered came, they merely shoved it in my face without saying a word! A very unprofessional and basically rude staff for an a supposed upscale restaurant!

I agree with the theme that a lot of other reviews have stated. A+ for the location, atmosphere, and service and a B+ for the actual food. We timely and inviting service (shoutout to Scott!) including a complimentary dessert with a candle for my dads birthday. The Christmas decorations and environment were very nice. Great variety of dishes to choose from for sure but the actual food was good but not 5 stars good. Overall flavors were nothing to write home about and most dishes were served not very hot. Disappointing considering the prices they put on everything. Would go back but there are plenty of other restaurants with way more flavorful dishes for cheaper prices in New Orleans.
My new favorite.   Service is impeccable, the food is tasty and excellent presentation.   I love the truffles they bring you at the end.
We eat here every time we go to NOLA; the steak is possibly the best we ever have.
Best dinner I've had in a long time!! Foie grass scallops -whoa!!!
Amazing food and an amazing atmosphere for an equally amazing price... lol.  It was definitely worth it though!!

Quite a hefty menu. Wait staff was excellent. However, the actual food was so so. Salads were anemic. The entrees were decent, with the fish and steak as the strong points. Cocktails were solid. Overall given the price I would have expected a bit more from the kitchen.
Fun experience & great food!
Loved the food and service

With out a doubt the best place we have had the pleasure to eat in the quarter. It would be a disservice if you did not eat here. Not enough words to describe our experience. Please reserve a table and enjoy.
Wonderful meal, and the price was amazing. Everything from the quality of service to the coffee was amazing. I cannot recommend this restaurant high enough.

In a word, disappointing, especially after all the positive things I had read. Perhaps because it was Christmas Day...but the service was mediocre. Some of the dishes were quite good, especially the roasted oysters, but not all. The filet I would not recommend. Just not the excellent experience we were expecting.

The ambience here is great, love the holiday feeling and the beautiful curtains. Their crab beignets and duck were amazing. The service was fine as well, they were fairly attentive. Only three stars though because we were there for a special occasion and they did nothing to acknowledge it.
Best place to eat in New Orleans, the food and service was excellent. Will definitely return.
This place is amazing. The service was excellent.

Well decorated comfortable setting with a lively bar scene. Robust wine offerings. The blue crab beignet was very good. All the food was actually really nice. The water service was great. Sometimes the wait for a glass of wine got a bit too long. Some fine tuning on service and management would get this another star.
Amazing.
Service was outstanding
Exquisite taste and service

The best gastronomic experience NOLA has to offer. Do not sleep on Restaurant R'evolution if you are in the vicinity. From the second you walk in the door you will experience service from people who are truly passionate about your experience and love what they do. To start with they have delicious and creative cocktails, along with the classics, if you cant choose from their more than impressive wine selection. You wont even have to wait for appetizers because you are greeted with bread service of house made bread and butter. There is a whole cheese cart and beautiful house made charcuteries drying in visible coolers in parts of the dining room Our meal was amazing, I was moved to tears by how perfectly everything was cooked and paired. The plank redfish was succulent and smokey and the scallops were cooked to perfection. I wish we would have had time to enjoy their full dessert selection but we were still treated to a handmade jewelry box, each compartment containing a small desert just for visiting.  I would have eaten here more on our trip had I known how good it was earlier. Do yourself a favor and go eat here.

The crab beignet are the best. Brunch here was outstanding.
Best meal in years
The ambiance is phenomenal in this restaurant.  We had a private room with approximately 10 people next to the wine cellar. Food was good but the service is what made this place exceptional.

The service is always amazing - 10/10 - however, lately the food seems to be hit or miss. The last time I went, the gumbo was much saltier than I remember and the dressing on my salad was overdone, soaking the lettuce and dominating the dish. The lobster gnocchi is a standout and so are the seared scallops. Drinks are some of the best in the city, including R'evolution's twist on an Old Fashioned with charred citrus. However, the best part of the meal for me is ordering some after dinner cocktails and indulging in the dessert box! So good!
Beautiful!

Decor lacks cohesion — one room is almost diner-like while another has white table cloths, and yet another has bare wood tables with darker lighting. Service was okay, but sloppy (prickly when we didn’t like a cocktail, forgot our potatoes au gratin, dirty napkin from previous guests under our table, butter served but no bread until first course arrived, etc) — food was just not special — salad was good but avg, crab beignets were good but super rich, lobster and gnocchi was too soft and over rich, ribeye was good, and desert was ok (peanut butter crunch ice cream was the best). We were underwhelmed at best.

A must do restaurant for any foodie! The Service was exceptional! Highly recommend the Chef Table to catch all of the kitchen's delicious food being prepared and served. The menu is a who's who of Nawlins traditional dishes with modern flare. It's our third yearly visit to this place and just like the other two times, we can't wait for our next year's visit. Bon appetit!
Food and service is AMAZING! Highly recommend!

This place is amazing. We made up our own "tasting menu" which included the turtle soup, quail, fois gras, frog leg BLT, and more. Every single dish impressed and the wine list was incredible. They also have some excellent cocktails if you have time to get there early and have a drink at the bar. They do have some very expensive items if you have cash to burn, which we didn't, however I felt for the total price and the quality of the food we got it was great a value, unlike some similar restaurants. The staff was also incredibly friendly and not stuffy like you might expect.
Great staff, creative menu and cocktails.

We came in for our honeymoon and my wife's birthday and had an absolutely amazing meal. Everyone was super attentive to us. We had the pig out board and a cheese plate to start. They were absolutely to die for. Our main course was even better. Everything was perfect. This was definitely the highlight of our time here. Thank you all so much for making our meal an event we will remember for years to come!
Great atmosphere, even better food!
EXCEPTIONAL!! From the door and back to the door again, service was impeccable! I cannot recommend R'evolution enough so do yourself a favor and get yo self down for a little palate pampering!!

If I could give more than 5 stars I would. The staff was attentive, friendly, and exceeded every expectation we had. I don't think my drink ever got below half full. The meal was hands down the best I have ever had. The dining areas were absolutely stunning. It gives a very romantic and upscale vibe. We went to celebrate my birthday and our recent marriage and they came out with two deserts and champagne as a gift. I can't say enough about this place! If you're looking for a romantic night out, go here. I don't believe there is another place in New Orleans that could even remotely compare!
Loved everything. Great food. Fantastic service. Bar drinks were very very good. Skilled staff throughout! 9k97

Visited during happy hour for some beers and snacks ar the bar. Few beers available but cocktails certainly looked like better value for money. The Crab Beignets were so good we immediately ordered a second portion of them. One of the better happy hours in the quarter
Top notch all around
Amazing experience
Great food and service. Wine priced fairly.

This place doesn’t need any more people raving about the food (even though it WAS fantastic) but what made our night so special was the service. Collin is incredibly personable and great at what he does. He brought such great energy to our table! Also I think we ordered everything he recommended because he’s so good at hyping up the food (and it doesn’t disappoint).  Also saw some famous people there which is always fun!
Service is excellent, the food was incredible!!
Tasty food! A little pricey and small portion, nut ots common for restaurants like this. Service is great.
Very pretentious and overpriced.

One of the most if not the most impressive and delicious meals and dining experiences we had during our stay in New Orleans! The restaurant itself is beautiful consisting of multiple themed rooms, we sat in the kitchen room and just loved it. Our waiter Deshaun was extremely friendly and knowledgeable helping us choose from an extensive menu based upon our tastes. I started with the turtle soup with quail eggs, beautifully presented and equally delicious. My wife had a deliciously light and beautiful crab beiegnets appetizer, which was like nothing either of of have ever experienced, just delicious. For our main course I had 3 variations of quail while my better half had a delicious shrimp and tasso risotto which she loved. Choose anything you'd like from the menu I'm certain they're equal delicious and all beautifully presented. Although we just returned we're both already looking forward to returning and revolutions will definitely be one of the restaurants we plan to revisit.
Fantastic food. Excellent service.
Always Fantastic
Excellent food and service. If you're looking for a night out on the town with New Orleans style fine dining, this would be a great place.
Excellent food!  Knowledgeable, courteous, prompt staff.  Atmosphere is fantastic old New Orleans style without the dusty dreeriness of an old restaurant.

If I had to pick 1 restaurant in NOLA to visit, this would be the one! Service from Rory and his team was impeccable; steak was cooked to perfection; and the setting was just beautiful. We had gorgeous cocktails in the bar just before heading in for dinner...then walked through beautiful dining rooms, all just a bit different to reach our table. The beer battered crab beignet and the oysters were outstanding. Our steaks were absolute perfection...filet and a ribeye. Go...you will not be disappointed!!

The little complimentary chest of candies & cookies they bring you at the end of your meal we're all delicious. They rounded out your meal perfectly, and such a fun touch!We wish we had room and time for dessert but we were stuffed and running behind schedule. We'll definitely have to try out their dessert menu another day!
Very small portions, taste was ok but nothing impressive

Food was delicious, and worth the price but service and decor felt like it came from 7 different places.  Uneven and expensive, just not what one would expect from a high end place, although food and drink alone would have gotten 5 stars
Good food, excellent service
Fantastic! Food was exceptional!  The entire staff was positive, smiling, engaged their customers and enjoyed their job One of the best meals I have had. You have to go to revolution!!!!!!!!!
Great bartenders.  Crab cake beignets excellent.  Wine list could be the best in the city with a knowledgeable staff.   Hey!  They have tvs too.  Asknto watch the game.
Great

The service was excellent, the staff were extremely accommodating and all the food was great. The setting and atmosphere was very romantic, sophisticated and upscale so I would recommend this to anyone [who [admittedly has the budget].
The staff told us about local events since we were from out of town. We were in town for my special birthday celebration and they made it very special indeed!
Great service and delicious food. Truly the best biscuit I have ever eaten.

This was our first visit to the Restaurant R'evolution on our first night in New Orleans.  It is located in the French Quarter section of New Orleans.  The first thing that I noticed when I approached the restaurant was that there was no neon sign identifying it, the sign was lit by the street light, the same way that the shops on the street have been lighted since the 1800's.  I can only describe this restaurant as elegant.  Your every need is addressed from the time you enter to the time you leave.  All the food is cooked to perfection and served in style.  Service is provided by a team of servers, so your everything is on time.  After our cocktails were served and we were reviewing the menu, we were served a Veal amuse-bouche, a gift from the Chef.  It was delicious.  The Fiorchatta bread was served with a sweet butter, regular butter and Virgin Olive Oil.  I could have made a meal out of the combination of Fiorchatta bread and sweet butter alone.  For an appetizer I had Oysters on the Half Shell R'evolution Style: Radish Chimichurri Salsa and Bloody Mary Granita.  A really unique taste for a person who normally likes his oysters plain, definitely worth another round.  For the main course we both had the 8-oz Filet Mignon with Gruyere Potato au Gratin.  I also had a side of Sautéed Mushrooms.  Both steaks were cooked to perfection.  Only a few steakhouses can properly prepare a Pittsburg style steak (charred on the outside with a cool red center) and the Restaurant R'evolution is one of them.  For desert my wife had the Creole Cream Cheese Bread Pudding Crème Brûlée.  It looked different from most bread puddings she has had, but she loved the taste.  I had a special desert called the Crown Royal, or something like that.  It was a brownie with a scoop of vanilla ice cream that had a center of peanut butter covered in chocolate with pecans, decant.  I also had a cup of Irish Coffee.  While preparing the bill, they gratuitously brought a 4 compartment "jewelry box" with baked treats in each compartment.  They don't want you to leave hungry.  Considering the ambience, service, quality of the food (especially the preparation of the steak) and the price, I have given them 5 stars and we will definitely be returning the next time we are in New Orleans and I highly recommend that if you get a chance experience this restaurant.
